CLIENT_ID=14d82eec-204b-4c2f-b7e8-296a70dab67e
TENANT_ID=common

# This is the official, global Application ID that Microsoft created for their own "Microsoft Graph PowerShell" tool.
# Because Microsoft published it globally as a "multi-tenant" application, it is available across all Microsoft 365
# environments. When you pair it with TENANT_ID=common, you are telling the Microsoft login screen: "Use the
# official Microsoft Graph PowerShell app, and figure out which company tenant I belong to based on the email address I type in."
#
# It's a very common "developer trick" to borrow this ID when you need to quickly test a script without
# having to ask your IT department to register a brand new application. Because it belongs to Microsoft,
# many IT departments leave it enabled by default, which is why it often works flawlessly out of the box!
